            <div type="translation">
                <p>The most venerable church of our Lady was erected by the contribution and the great desire of Ioannes Gerakiotes/Moutoullas and his wife Eirene, on the thirtieth of July of the year 6788 (1280).</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>The surname of the founder Ioannes became a subject of much debate between the scholars. Ιt is clear that the surname "Gerakiotes" was written first and then the surname "Moutoullas" was added above it. Only the first six letters of the surname "Gerakiotes" are clearly visible while the others have been overwritten with the last letters of the surname "Moutoullas". According to <bibl><ptr target="#Papageorgiou1975"></ptr></bibl>, the name "Gerakiοtes" refers to the place of origin of the donor, the "Gerakies", while the name "Moutoullas" is his surname. Gradually, it seems that the name of "Moutoullas" was also given to the village, which is why there was an attempt to erase "Gerakiotes" and replace it with "Moutoullas". Based on the greek manuscript 1129 (paris. gr. 1129) of the National Library of Paris (see <bibl><ptr target="#Darrouzès1950"></ptr>, <citedRange>184</citedRange></bibl>, <bibl><ptr target="#PerdikisMyrianthefs2009"></ptr>, <citedRange>49-51</citedRange></bibl>), it appears that for many years, until 1387, the church was known as the Church of Panagia of "Gerakiotes".

</p>
            </div>
